  "prompt": "What is the legislative branch responsible for? What is the publication of the legislative branch?",
  "response": "The legislative branch, typically represented by Congress in the United States, is responsible for:\n\n1. Creating, debating, and passing federal laws\n2. Levying taxes\n3. Declaring war\n4. Regulating commerce\n5. Approving the federal budget\n6. Conducting oversight of the executive branch\n7. Confirming presidential appointments\n8. Conducting investigations\n\nThe primary publication of the legislative branch is the Congressional Record, which is the official daily record of debates, proceedings, and votes in the United States Congress. It provides a comprehensive account of what is said and done on the floor of the House of Representatives and the Senate.",
